                            <comment id="13487018" author="zhihyu@ebaysf.com" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 17:03:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please refine your requirement a bit more.&lt;br/&gt;
Would the multiple applications belong to the same user (group) ?&lt;br/&gt;
If not, we have to consider fine-grained access control.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13487020" author="huhlig" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 17:06:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Had not thought on security for this use case. Out need in particular is for pig, hive, impala and map-reduce to be able to query table definitions without each having to be configured to understand the underlying table information. This request might not be necessary if these applications begin using HCatalog heavily and in a more agnostic manner.&lt;br/&gt;
Fine grain control to fields would probably be a wise idea but for our use case not necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13487026" author="zhihyu@ebaysf.com" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 17:15:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you can use HCatalog for accessing such metadata, that would be better.&lt;br/&gt;
Once this additional information goes into Table &amp;amp; Column Family definitions, we have to consider security support in a multi-tenant environment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13487035" author="sershe" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 17:28:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;CONFIG&quot; feature in the shell allows arbitrary user strings on tables and cfs. It&apos;s 0.96 only though.&lt;br/&gt;
I am not quite sure about how this is related to schema information fetching though. What kind of metadata do you have in mind?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13487047" author="huhlig" created="Tue, 30 Oct 2012 17:42:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Our biggest example was keeping the avro schema for hive, pig and impala inside the table descriptor.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13488288" author="stack" created="Wed, 31 Oct 2012 22:05:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=huhlig&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;huhlig&quot;&gt;Hans Uhlig&lt;/a&gt; Have you tried it using the CONFIG option Sergey notes above?   Would be interested in your experience.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
